| 3         | 30             | 30 →    | null         |
| 4         | null           | Stop    | Stop         |

# A trick to remember

Every Linked List traversal always follows this 3-step cycle:

```text
1. Start from head

2. Do some work (print)

3. Move to next node
```

```java
Node temp = head;

while(temp != null){

    // work

    temp = temp.next;
}
```

Bro, if you're writing notes, write this sentence in a box ⭐:

> **A Linked List is nothing but visiting one node at a time until we reach null.**
